data.chText: 属同时期的；同一时代的
我们没有当时人们对这一战役的记载。
data.enText: We have no contemporary account of the battle (= written near the time that it happened) .

data.chText: 他与剧作家康格里夫属于同一时代。
data.enText: He was contemporary with the dramatist Congreve.

data.chText: 当代小说 / 音乐 / 舞蹈

data.enText: a person who lives or lived at the same time as sb else, especially sb who is about the same age
She and I were contemporaries at college.

data.chText: 他是弗洛伊德的同代人，可能认识弗洛伊德。
data.enText: He was a contemporary of Freud and may have known him.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + tempor 时间 + ary …的 → 同时间的 → 同代的

tr: a person of nearly the same age as another

example: the role of computers in modern-day medicine

tr: occurring in the same period of time
example: a rise in interest rates is often contemporaneous with an increase in inflation
the composer Salieri was contemporary with Mozart

value.def: Contemporary things are modern and relate to the present time.

example.ex: She writes a lot of contemporary music for people like Whitney Houston...
example.tran: 她给像惠特尼·休斯敦这样的人写了很多当代音乐作品。

example.ex: Perhaps he should have a more updated look, a more contemporary style...
example.tran: 也许他应该有一个更新的形象，更具时代性的风格。

example.ex: Only the names are ancient; the characters are modern and contemporary.
example.tran: 只有姓名是古代的； 人物都是现代的、摩登的。

value.def: Contemporary people or things were alive or happened at the same time as something else you are talking about.

example.ex: ...drawing upon official records and the reports of contemporary witnesses.
example.tran: 利用官方的记录与当时的见证者的报告

value.tran: 同时发生的;同时期的;同时代的

value.def: Someone's contemporary is a person who is or was alive at the same time as them.

example.ex: Like most of my contemporaries, I grew up in a vastly different world.
example.tran: 和大多数同辈人一样，我生长在一个截然不同的世界。

example.ex: ...a glossary of musical terms found in Shakespeare and his contemporaries.
example.tran: 莎士比亚及其同时代人音乐术语汇编

value.tran: 同时期的人;同时代的人
